Name of Project:
Airline Safety – A Look at the Truth

Overview:
Transportation is an important part of our daily lives. However, the decision-making process regarding how we travel often revolves around safety. Many individuals have fears about flying due to high-profile accidents and media coverage, despite statistics indicating it’s safer than driving. 
This project focused on comparing the safety of airline travel with driving, emphasizing the lower risk associated with flying. It comprises of a blog post, dashboard, and an informative infographic. These components collectively aim to highlight publicly available data to demonstrate why individuals should feel more confident and secure when opting for air travel over driving. 

Programs Used:
This project utilized PowerBI to create the visualizations. 
